  "texts": [
    "GNNs not only take into account the variables present in the dataset modeled as node attributes, but they exploit the topology of the graph by considering the links between patients (i.e. between nodes).",
    "Despite data on a single patient may be scarce, similarity with other patients could aid in correct prioritisation.",
    "In addition, our approach not only provides a novel design but also offers reusable and available code, whose accessibility is specified in the dedicated section.",
    "Our approach offers an inductive embedding, enabling the addition of novel patients to the graph for classification 33, 34.",
    "We evaluated our pipeline using public data to demonstrate its effectiveness and improvement over state-of-the-art approaches."
  ]
}